1
00:01:51,195 --> 00:01:53,784
又有三个人今早跑了
Three more gone this morning.

2
00:01:54,974 --> 00:01:57,513
都是贱民
Outcasts and idiots.

3
00:01:57,543 --> 00:02:00,202
他们都变得躁动不安，在战争结束的时候
They all get restless. With the fighting done,

4
00:02:00,242 --> 00:02:01,962
他们都想满载金币回家
they want to be home with money in their pockets,

5
00:02:02,002 --> 00:02:05,371
而不是静坐在这种令人消沉的寒冷又潮湿的地方
not sitting in this dismal cold and wet.

6
00:02:05,681 --> 00:02:07,361
优良的战士都没有跑
None of the good men have run.

7
00:02:07,401 --> 00:02:09,050
他们也不会
Nor will they.

8
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:11,620
他们也不会跟随你到罗马
Nor will they follow you to Rome.

9
00:02:11,660 --> 00:02:13,329
只是时候未到
Not yet.

10
00:02:13,369 --> 00:02:15,339
时间不多了
Time is running out.

11
00:02:16,419 --> 00:02:18,718
我们不能永远等在这里
We cannot wait here forever.

12
00:02:18,798 --> 00:02:21,777
现在是非常时期
This is a very precarious position.

13
00:02:21,807 --> 00:02:25,916
当一月份到来，你任职期限到期时，会发生什么？
What happens in January when your term runs out

14
00:02:25,966 --> 00:02:28,986
难道我们还坐在这里？
and we're still sitting here?

15
00:02:31,585 --> 00:02:34,614
去鼓动战士们打仗是一件微妙的事情，波卡
The business of motivating men to fight is a tricky matter, Posca.

16
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:38,683
我不期望一个奴隶能够明白其中的奥秘
I would not expect a slave to understand the subtleties.

17
00:02:38,763 --> 00:02:43,952
我相信他们很快就会懂了
I trust an education in these subtleties will begin shortly.

18
00:02:47,191 --> 00:02:49,071
500,000？这是什么？
500,000? What's this?

19
00:02:49,111 --> 00:02:51,610
我提名马克·安东尼竞选护民官
I put Mark Antony up for election as People's Tribune.

20
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,470
所以需要买很多人的选票
There were a lot of votes needed buying.

21
00:02:54,670 --> 00:02:58,079
让马克·安东尼当护民管？
Mark Antony for People's Tribune?

22
00:02:58,119 --> 00:02:59,718
但他
But he is--

23
00:02:59,768 --> 00:03:02,128
尽管说
 um...  You may speak.

24
00:03:02,188 --> 00:03:04,807
我明白护民管是一个很神圣的职位
I had understood the Tribune to be a sacred office

25
00:03:04,857 --> 00:03:07,137
拥有否决元老院的权利
with the power of veto over the Senate.

26
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:11,586
当然，一个非常高贵庄严的职位
So it is. An office of great dignity and seriousness.

27
00:03:11,626 --> 00:03:13,515
可能你是对的
Perhaps you're right.

28
00:03:14,165 --> 00:03:18,934
我们将会派斯特雷波前去确定安东尼行为良好
We shall send Strabo along to make sure Antony behaves himself.

29
00:03:32,271 --> 00:03:33,690
还有多远？
How far now?

30
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,470
还有三个小时的路程
Three hours at pace.

31
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:38,609
嘿！女孩们，我来了
Ah-hi! Here I come, girls.

32
00:03:38,659 --> 00:03:39,959
我要在城里喝遍所有的酒, 吸遍所有的烟
I'm going to drink all the wine, smoke all the smoke

33
00:03:39,959 --> 00:03:42,158
还要操遍所有的妓女
 and fuck every whore in the city.

34
00:03:42,178 --> 00:03:44,338
保持一点尊严，你还不够格
  Show some dignity.  You're under the standard.

35
00:03:44,368 --> 00:03:46,387
那好，去跟他说
 Well, talk to him.

36
00:03:48,157 --> 00:03:51,076
他不在此列
He's not under the standard.

37
00:03:51,696 --> 00:03:53,646
还有三小时某人就能见到八年没见面的妻子了
Three hours away from a wife he hasn't seen in eight years.

38
00:03:53,686 --> 00:03:57,175
他害怕了，重聚当然是令人高兴的
 The man's terrified.  Surely a reunion is a happy event.

39
00:03:57,205 --> 00:03:58,825
 谈些其他的  害怕了吧
 Talk of something else.  Terrified.

40
00:03:58,855 --> 00:04:01,764
万一她已经掉牙了？ 又或者变得骨瘦如材了？
What if she's lost her teeth? What if she's gotten skinny?

41
00:04:01,794 --> 00:04:03,733
万一她有同别的男人上过床了？
What if she's been letting other men between her legs?

42
00:04:03,810 --> 00:04:05,437
肃静！
Silence!

43
00:04:40,095 --> 00:04:43,024
他们喜欢他，对吗？ 没关系
 They love him, eh?  No matter.

44
00:04:43,064 --> 00:04:45,124
我们都是有地位的人
We are all men of substance.

45
00:04:45,164 --> 00:04:48,703
让他们去拥有平民和穷人的爱戴吧
Let them have the love of the plebs and the proles.

46
00:04:58,141 --> 00:04:59,890
这不会持续很久，对吧？
This won't take long, will it?

47
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,790
希望如此，上帝
We can hope, Dominus.

48
00:05:01,820 --> 00:05:04,989
 乌瑞纳斯，你可以解散他们了  遵命
 vorenus, you may dismiss the men.  Sir.

49
00:05:05,009 --> 00:05:07,948
然后你自己也解散，直到我有任务给你
And then you may dismiss yourself until I send for you.

50
00:05:07,978 --> 00:05:09,408
去找点乐子
Have some fun.

51
00:05:09,438 --> 00:05:12,717
但首先，带着个男孩回
But first, take the boy back to Atia.

52
00:05:12,747 --> 00:05:14,917
拿回你们的报酬
Get your reward, eh?

53
00:05:14,957 --> 00:05:19,416
孩子，告诉你可爱的母亲，我呆会儿会去见她
Boy, tell your lovely mother I will see her later.

54
00:05:20,275 --> 00:05:22,755
让我们把这些办完
Let's get this over with.

55
00:05:29,595 --> 00:05:31,256
Shh!

56
00:05:38,801 --> 00:05:40,461
你，现在马上离开这屋！
You, leave this house this moment.

57
00:05:40,501 --> 00:05:42,730
我不会，屋大维是我名正言顺的妻子
I will not. Octavia is my rightful wife.

58
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,010
 你敢违抗恺撒？  恺撒算什么！
 You defy Caesar?  A fig for Caesar!

59
00:05:45,050 --> 00:05:47,359
以五复仇女神的名义，如果我不是一位上流社会的女士
By the five furies, if I were not a genteel woman,

60
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:50,908
我会将你的皮剥掉，然后吊起来挂在门上
I would have you flayed and hung from a bracket at the door!

61
00:05:50,938 --> 00:05:52,518
卡斯特？ 什么事，主人？
 Castor?  Domina?

62
00:05:52,548 --> 00:05:54,817
把狗牵来
Fetch the dogs!

63
00:05:58,347 --> 00:06:00,806
傲慢无耻的卑鄙小人！
Insolent wretch!

64
00:06:00,976 --> 00:06:03,425
我告诉你，亲爱的，你已经和那人没有任何关系了
I tell you, my honey, you are well rid of that one.

65
00:06:03,455 --> 00:06:04,665
我恨你
I hate you.

66
00:06:04,695 --> 00:06:06,955
我恨你！我恨你！
I hate you! I hate you!

67
00:06:07,674 --> 00:06:09,684
愚蠢的女孩
Silly girl.

68
00:06:21,141 --> 00:06:23,951
我仅仅是尽全力为她着想，为什么她不明白？
I'm only trying to do my best for her. Why can't she see that?

69
00:06:23,971 --> 00:06:24,840
她还小
She is young.

70
00:06:24,890 --> 00:06:27,810
屋大维主人驾到！ 我亲爱的孩子！
 Master Octavian!  Baby boy!

71
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:30,109
我可怜的小兔崽子！
My poor rabbit!

72
00:06:30,189 --> 00:06:32,214
Oh!

73
00:06:33,808 --> 00:06:37,757
真瘦，旅途很艰辛吧！
So thin. Was it very horrible?

74
00:06:37,797 --> 00:06:39,357
当然，我想都不敢想
Of course it was, I can't even imagine.

75
00:06:39,387 --> 00:06:40,847
我们不要再谈论这个了
We shan't even talk about it.

76
00:06:40,877 --> 00:06:43,626
就把旅途的事完完全全的抛在脑后
We should just put it totally out of our minds.

77
00:06:43,676 --> 00:06:46,215
现在的安全到家就好了
You're back safe at home now.

78
00:06:48,415 --> 00:06:50,784
那些人是谁？
But who are those?

79
00:06:50,864 --> 00:06:52,594
你应该对他们非常好，母亲
You are to be very good to them, Mother.

80
00:06:52,624 --> 00:06:54,793
他们是我特殊的朋友
They are particular friends of mine.

81
00:06:54,813 --> 00:06:57,233
朋友？怎样特殊？
Friends? In what particular?

82
00:06:57,463 --> 00:07:00,062
是他们把被囚禁的我给解救出来的
These are the men that took me from captivity.

83
00:07:00,112 --> 00:07:03,321
首先是枪兵百夫长，卢西尔斯·乌瑞纳斯
First Spear Centurion Lucius Vorenus.

84
00:07:04,081 --> 00:07:06,411
这位是兵团士兵，泰特斯·波罗
And LegionaryTitus Pullo.

85
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,650
我们欢迎你们
So, we embrace you.

86
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:11,679
你们真叫人敬畏
Good fearsome specimens you are.

87
00:07:11,729 --> 00:07:14,769
我想你们征服那些讨厌的高卢人一定花了很长时间吧
I wonder it took you so long to subdue those odious Gauls.

88
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:16,838
他们人数非常多，夫人
There was a great many of them, ma'am.

89
00:07:16,878 --> 00:07:19,458
非常多…不错
Great many- very good.

90
00:07:19,508 --> 00:07:20,677
那我们就走了，女士
We'll be away then, sir.

91
00:07:20,707 --> 00:07:22,647
噢，但在你们走之前，你们一定要接受嘉赏
Oh, but you must be rewarded before you go.

92
00:07:22,677 --> 00:07:25,116
 卡斯特，把我的钱包拿来  那不必要
 Castor, bring me my purse.  That won't be necessary.

93
00:07:25,166 --> 00:07:26,976
不行吗？我没有破坏你们的纪律
Will it not? I don't want to break any regulations--

94
00:07:27,036 --> 00:07:28,295
他们应该留下来吃点东西，母亲
They shall stay and eat, Mother.

95
00:07:28,335 --> 00:07:30,435
当然，面包和肉都在厨房里面
Of course! There shall be bread and meat put out in the kitchen.

96
00:07:30,475 --> 00:07:32,155
我指他们应该和我们一同进餐
I mean, they shall eat with us.

97
00:07:32,474 --> 00:07:36,154
遵命，先生，但我要去找我的妻子
Obliged, sir, but I must go to my wife.

98
00:07:36,154 --> 00:07:38,953
你妻子已经等了八年，可以多等一下
Your wife has waited eight years. She can wait a little longer.

99
00:07:39,143 --> 00:07:41,112
凯撒已经给了他们荣誉坐骑
Caesar has given them honorary horses,

100
00:07:41,152 --> 00:07:42,632
他们还骑着马，拿着军旗回来
and they ride with the standard.

101
00:07:42,652 --> 00:07:45,451
和他们一同进餐是完全可以接受的
It's perfectly acceptable to eat with them.

102
00:07:45,481 --> 00:07:47,461
真是绝妙的主意
Splendid idea.

103
00:07:47,731 --> 00:07:52,400
值得纪念，我们今晚将平等的享受晚餐
It's symbolic. We shall all dine together as equals.

104
00:07:56,739 --> 00:07:58,888
那是什么声音？ 哦，那是你妹妹
 What's that?  Oh, it's just your sister.

105
00:07:58,908 --> 00:08:01,138
 他没事吧？  妇女之事
 Is she all right?  Women's troubles.

106
00:08:01,168 --> 00:08:03,497
哭哭就好了
Nothing a good leeching won't cure.

107
00:08:12,185 --> 00:08:16,484
朱庇特·凡尔格神啊，我们请求你指引并保护这个人
Jupiter Fulgor, we ask you to guide and protect this man,

108
00:08:16,514 --> 00:08:20,543
马克·安东尼，新任护民管
Marcus Antonius, newly elected Tribune of plebs,

109
00:08:20,573 --> 00:08:23,093
以及人民的英雄
champion of the people.

110
00:08:23,143 --> 00:08:24,982
总共杀了多少人？
How many dead altogether?

111
00:08:25,822 --> 00:08:29,041
我不知道，早就数不清了
I don't know. I lost count ages ago.

112
00:08:29,081 --> 00:08:31,071
不过很多
Lots though.

113
00:08:31,331 --> 00:08:32,230
那你喃，卢西尔斯？
And you, Lucius?

114
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:35,350
309个战士，没有算过有多少平民
309 fighting men. I don't keep count on civilians.

115
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:37,619
你记得真清楚 战争神殿需要你在
 You're very exact.  The war temple requires

116
00:08:37,649 --> 00:08:39,599
供奉时给一个具体的数目
an exact number when you make an offering.

117
00:08:39,629 --> 00:08:41,908
那就意味着要捐很多的酒和羊
That's a lot of wine and goats.

118
00:08:42,488 --> 00:08:46,367
如果你超过100,牧师们会给你些折扣
The priests offer a discount when you pass 100.

119
00:08:46,397 --> 00:08:48,377
牧师！他们多数都是骗子
Priests! Crooks, many of them.

120
00:08:48,417 --> 00:08:51,056
要是我，我就直接同上帝对话
I just talk direct to whatever God I'm doing business with.

121
00:08:51,086 --> 00:08:53,076
作呕的牧师！
Bugger the priests!

122
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:55,145
很少有人会在意
Too few people can be bothered to do things

123
00:08:55,165 --> 00:08:57,545
以正统的罗马方式来处理事情
the proper, all-Roman way.

124
00:08:57,585 --> 00:09:00,814
我对你的做法表示欣赏，卢西尔斯·乌瑞纳斯是位严格的卡托追随者
 I commend you, Lucius.  vorenus is a strict Catonian.

125
00:09:00,834 --> 00:09:02,673
我相信共和国的神灵
I believe in the divinity of the Republic.

126
00:09:02,703 --> 00:09:06,612
如果卡托和我的信仰一样，那我想我应该就是他的追随者
If Cato believes the same, then I suppose I am a Catonian.

127
00:09:06,652 --> 00:09:09,272
但卡托代表的是贵族们的权利
But Cato represents the rights of the nobility.

128
00:09:09,302 --> 00:09:13,151
像你这样的平民肯定希望能发生一些改变
Surely a plebian like yourself would like to see some changes made.

129
00:09:13,211 --> 00:09:16,220
在共和国成立时是什么样，现在就应该是什么样
It should remain as it was at the founding of the Republic.

130
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,449
为什么要改变它？
Why should that change?

131
00:09:17,456 --> 00:09:19,048
因为罗马人民在受苦
Because the Roman people are suffering.

132
00:09:19,279 --> 00:09:21,419
因为奴隶们要做所有的活
Because slaves have taken all the work.

133
00:09:21,449 --> 00:09:23,708
因为贵族们占有了所有的地
Because nobles have taken all the land,

134
00:09:23,738 --> 00:09:26,158
而且遍街都是无家可归和饥饿的人们
and the streets are full of the homeless and the starving.

135
00:09:26,198 --> 00:09:28,397
噢，我还不知道我的孩子是这样的一个煽动者
Well, I had no idea my son was such a firebrand.

136
00:09:28,427 --> 00:09:30,547
贵族们说凯撒是个战犯
The nobles say that Caesar is a war criminal.

137
00:09:30,577 --> 00:09:33,146
他们说他想要踏步走回罗马封自己为王
They say that he wishes to march on Rome and make himself king.

138
00:09:33,166 --> 00:09:35,926
那是亵渎神灵的行为，没人会跟随他的
That is sacrilege. No man of honor would follow him.

139
00:09:35,956 --> 00:09:39,665
恩，那我就失礼了，我会说凯撒应该骑着大象冲回这里
Well, I'm no man of honor then, 'cause I say that Caesar should ride in here

140
00:09:39,715 --> 00:09:43,614
把庞贝、卡托以及其他那些相当国王的人给压扁
with elephants and squash Pompey and Cato and anybody else that wants it.

141
00:09:43,644 --> 00:09:45,563
去他的法律，我就这样认为
Never mind the law. That's what I say.

142
00:09:45,593 --> 00:09:47,163
你这样说是应为你不仅理智有问题
You say that because you govern your reason

143
00:09:47,203 --> 00:09:49,352
还管不住你的嘴
no better than you govern your tongue.

144
00:09:49,392 --> 00:09:52,772
不好意思，是我的错，让大家在喝酒时讨论政治
Forgive me, it's my fault for mixing politics and wine.

145
00:09:52,812 --> 00:09:55,951
还要多些丁鲷吗？或来只榛睡鼠？
More tench? A dormouse perhaps?

146
00:09:55,981 --> 00:09:57,161
谢谢，我够了
Thank you, I won't.

147
00:09:57,201 --> 00:09:58,570
别把我说的放在心上
Don't mind my saying it,

148
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:02,159
但你们确实不是志同道合的朋友
but you two make unlikely friends.

149
00:10:02,219 --> 00:10:04,329
我们不是朋友关系，我是他的上司
We are not friends. I am his superior officer.

150
00:10:04,359 --> 00:10:05,848
只是从等级划分来看
By virtue of rank, if nothing else.

151
00:10:05,878 --> 00:10:08,728
你已经说够了！
That is enough from you!

152
00:10:10,897 --> 00:10:12,257
请原谅我们鲁莽的行为，夫人
Please forgive our vulgar ways, madam.

153
00:10:12,307 --> 00:10:14,337
我们在你面前显得很不得体
We are not fit for your presence.

154
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,896
没关系，和你们的相处让我感到无比高兴
Not at all. I've enjoyed your company immensely.

155
00:10:16,926 --> 00:10:18,675
非常与众不同
It's been most refreshing.

156
00:10:18,715 --> 00:10:21,125
如果你同意，我们就…
And with your permission, we shall...

157
00:10:21,215 --> 00:10:22,994
离开了
Ieave you.

158
00:10:24,914 --> 00:10:26,674
有空再来玩
Do come and visit us again.

159
00:10:26,714 --> 00:10:29,143
屋大维需要可信赖的朋友
Octavian needs reliable friends.

160
00:10:29,193 --> 00:10:30,843
他可能得依靠你们，我相信
He may depend on you, I trust.

161
00:10:30,893 --> 00:10:32,702
如你所愿，夫人
As you say, madam.

162
00:10:41,830 --> 00:10:44,299
 再说一次？  我什么都没说
 Say again?  I did not speak.

163
00:10:44,759 --> 00:10:46,719
我走这边
I go this way.

164
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:49,618
我的家就在那条染色坊街的后面，如果你有什么需要…
My home is behind the street of the cloth dyers, if you--

165
00:10:49,668 --> 00:10:51,888
祝你好运，长官
Go with fortune, sir.

166
00:10:54,587 --> 00:10:56,427
比较干净点的妓院
